because he was really sick.

561
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:20,451
What was supposed to be a weekend visit

562
00:35:21,285 --> 00:35:23,121
turned into a four-month stay.

563
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:29,001
I'm just happy someone was there
to be with him in the end.

564
00:35:29,627 --> 00:35:31,045
Oh, my God, Brad.

565
00:35:31,671 --> 00:35:33,381
I wish you could've met him.

566
00:35:34,423 --> 00:35:35,758
What was he like?

567
00:35:36,884 --> 00:35:37,884
Stubborn.

568
00:35:38,386 --> 00:35:40,263
Mm-hm. Charming.

569
00:35:41,806 --> 00:35:44,016
Self-loathing, self-deprecating.

570
00:35:45,351 --> 00:35:46,686
Ahem. Yeah, I know.

571
00:35:47,478 --> 00:35:49,564
I mean, uh, apple/tree, right?

572
00:35:51,065 --> 00:35:52,984
It helped to know that he'd thought of me.

573
00:35:53,609 --> 00:35:54,986
And he was proud of me.

574
00:35:56,529 --> 00:35:58,239
He told me his side of what happened.

575
00:36:00,449 --> 00:36:02,618
He and my mom were so young
when they had me.

576
00:36:03,870 --> 00:36:05,830
He was doing all kinds of drugs.

577
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:08,749
Thought I'd be better off without him.

578
00:36:10,459 --> 00:36:11,961
By the time he got clean,

579
00:36:12,795 --> 00:36:14,297
he assumed I hated him.

580
00:36:15,131 --> 00:36:17,341
Was too scared to find out
if he was right.

581
00:36:18,426 --> 00:36:20,428
Then he started seeing
my name in the papers.

582
00:36:21,762 --> 00:36:23,931
He didn't think I'd wanna hear from him.

583
00:36:25,766 --> 00:36:28,853
All that success
I wanted to impress him with...

584
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:32,481
was the thing that was keeping him away.

585
00:36:35,318 --> 00:36:37,111
He followed my career though.

586
00:36:37,737 --> 00:36:39,947
Could tell me most of the people
I'd worked with,

587
00:36:40,615 --> 00:36:43,117
even played me
a song I produced on his guitar.

588
00:36:46,787 --> 00:36:47,788
All of that...

589
00:36:49,707 --> 00:36:50,707
anger...

590
00:36:52,668 --> 00:36:54,462
and the fear, it just...

591
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:05,222
Hmph.

592
00:37:08,768 --> 00:37:10,353
It just disappeared.

593
00:37:14,982 --> 00:37:16,651
I was dying to call you.

594
00:37:18,444 --> 00:37:19,987
But I knew I had no right.

595
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:24,700
But still, I need you to know
that none of that...

596
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:28,829
would have happened without you.

597
00:37:31,707 --> 00:37:34,377
I've waited so long to hear you say this.

598
00:37:38,339 --> 00:37:40,383
I don't want to be like my dad.

599
00:37:44,011 --> 00:37:46,222
Dying alone without the woman I love.

600
00:37:50,226 --> 00:37:52,728
Why couldn't you be this person
when we were together?

601
00:37:53,354 --> 00:37:54,772
If I hadn't met you...

602
00:37:58,025 --> 00:37:59,986
I wouldn't be this person at all.

603
00:38:07,118 --> 00:38:08,828
Do you wanna get out of here?

604
00:38:15,751 --> 00:38:16,751
Okay.

605
00:38:17,628 --> 00:38:19,630
